cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the stability and generalization of graph convolutional neural networks (GCNNs) in a semi-supervised graph learning setting. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of GCNNs for various learning tasks on graph data also relates to computer vision (cs.CV) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the analysis of the largest absolute eigenvalue of the graph convolution filter is a concept commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
